In this article, President Trump and Henry Kissinger hold a meeting in the Oval Office. Trump speaks highly of Kissinger and the progress they have made in the Middle East. When asked about Senator Corker's comment about World War III, Trump states that they were on the wrong path before and that they are now on the right path. He also addresses the issue of tax reform, saying that the American people want tax cuts and that he is giving the largest tax cuts in history. He mentions bringing back $3 trillion from offshore and announces that he will be signing something soon to provide healthcare for people who have been hurt by Obamacare. Trump denies undercutting anyone and expresses confidence in Secretary Tillerson. The article concludes with the end of the meeting.